         <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.1931" xml:lang="en">
            <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
            <pb facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/>
            <dateline>Colombo, 22 February 1890</dateline>
            <opener>Dear Sir,</opener>
            <p>I send you some more books by Jansz. Sorry. Some are so dirty. I learn that he is paralysed and can write no more; but he has some more works in manuscript that he would be glad to sell. I shall see what he wants for them. I hope to get the words of the Caffrinha soon, and shall send them to you.</p>
            <closer>
               <salute>Yours very truly</salute>
               <lb/>
               <signed>
                  <persName ref="[authorityLink]">Donald Ferguson</persName>
               </signed>
            </closer>
         </div>
